cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SD 

The paper proposes a deep neural network model for generating dynamic population distributions from coarse population data, which involves both spatial and temporal patterns. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is computer vision (cs.CV) as the model utilizes super-resolution convolutional neural network (SRCNN) to map coarse data into higher resolution data. The model also involves deep learning techniques such as long short-term memory (LSTM) and is trained using a real-life mobile dataset, which suggests that machine learning (cs.LG) and social and information networks (cs.SI) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with population distribution, which could fall under the sub-categories of computational geometry (cs.CG) or computational social science (cs.CY). Finally, the paper involves time series analysis, which could fall under the sub-category of statistics (cs.SD).
